import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import json

def scraper(url):
    # get webpage content
    page = requests.get(url)

    # create BeautifulSoup object
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page.content, 'html.parser')

    # find all job listings
    listings = soup.find_all('li', class_="posting")

    # initialize empty list to store data
    data = []

    # loop through job listings
    for listing in listings:
        # extract title, tag and apply link from the listing
        title = listing.find('h5', class_="posting-company").text.strip()
        tag = listing.find('a', class_="posting-category").text.strip()
        apply_link = listing.find('div', class_="posting-btn-submit").a['href']

        # store data in a dictionary
        entry = {
            'title': title,
            'tag': tag,
            'apply_link': apply_link,
        }

        # append dictionary to data list
        data.append(entry)

    # print data in JSON format
    print(json.dumps(data, indent=4))

if __name__ == '__main__':
    url = "https://jobs.lever.co/appboxo"
    scraper(url)
